Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water
to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

Put the @Crumbled Blue Cheese{30%g} and the @Breadcrumbs{25%g} in a #bowl{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in the @Olive Oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb, then set your blue
cheese crumb aside for later.

Halve any large @Cauliflower Florets{300%g} and pop them into an #ovenproof dish{}. Drizzle
with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a
single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

When the cauli is halfway through roasting, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g}
to the dish and roast for the remaining amount of time, until golden.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, stir in the @Macaroni{180%g} and bring
back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and
stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, melt the @Butter{20%g} in a saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once the butter has melted, stir in the @Plain Flour{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until it
forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Gradually stir in the @Water{250%ml} for the sauce and the @Vegetable Stock Paste{15%g}.
Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the grated cheese to the sauce and stir until melted.

Next, stir the roasted cauli, bacon and cooked pasta through the sauce, then pour back
into the ovenproof dish.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Turn your #grill{} on to high.

Sprinkle the blue cheese crumb evenly over the top, then grill the mac and cheese on the
top shelf of your oven until the crumb is golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Serve your mac and cheese in bowls, sprinkle over the @Walnuts{40%g} and drizzle the
@Sriracha Sauce{15%g} over the top.

> Add less sriracha if you'd prefer things milder.

Enjoy!